@hcaseyal 

This is the proto definition we used:
syntax = "proto3";

package myrpc;

service MsgTransfer {
  rpc SendMsg (stream MyMsg) returns (stream MyMsg) {}
}

message MyMsg {
  bytes msg = 1;
}


This is how we do read:
readMsg.reset(new myrpc::MyMsg);
  clientData->stream->Read(readMsg.get(), reinterpret_cast<void *>(this));

We used bidi stream async mode, same as the async server and async client example.  Found that if client doesn’t disconnect, the stream hold quite a lot of memory.
